 =\n0.81$. A $Q^2$-dependent error analysis of the neutrino data shows that the\nuncertainties in the axial form factor $G_A(Q^2)$ are comparable to the ones\ninduced by the a priori half width rule. We identify the most sensitive region\nto be in the range $0.2 \\lesssim Q^2 \\lesssim 0.6 \\,{\\rm GeV}^2$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Oct 2015 16:13:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 5 Feb 2016 11:56:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-09"}
