 the original GNM and\nANM methods. We further demonstrate benefit of our mGNM in the B-factor\npredictions on many proteins that fail the original GNM method. We show that\nthe present mGNM can also be used to analyze protein domain separations.\nFinally, we showcase the ability of our mANM for the simulation of protein\ncollective motions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Oct 2015 21:47:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-20"}
