e results it is\nentirely possible that the inflation of solar cycle amplitudes in the backbone\ngroup sunspot number as one goes back in time, relative to related\nsolar-terrestrial parameters, is entirely caused by the use of inappropriate\nand non-robust regression techniques to calibrate the sunspot data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Oct 2015 08:28:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 10 Nov 2015 10:58:04 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 24 Jan 2016 22:13:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-23"}
