n20000 are needed to investigate water in protoplanetary disks. Intrinsic\ndifferences in disk structure, e.g. inner gaps, gas-to-dust ratio, dust size\nand distribution, and inner disk scale height, between Herbig and TTauri star\ndisks are able to explain a lower water detection rate in disks around Herbig\nstars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Oct 2015 15:58:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-23"}
